		`

		<description><![CDATA[Novel excerpts and short stories by Tanya Tagaq, Heather O’Neill, Sam Shelstad, and more]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img width="1600" height="1067" src="https://walrus-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/img/ArchivalIssue_2023_Roundup_1800_02_Fiction.jpg" class="webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image" alt="A blue background with text that reads Our Best Fiction" loading="lazy" style="display: block; margin-bottom: 5px; clear:both;max-width: 100%;" link_thumbnail="" srcset="https://walrus-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/img/ArchivalIssue_2023_Roundup_1800_02_Fiction.jpg 1600w, https://walrus-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/img/ArchivalIssue_2023_Roundup_1800_02_Fiction-735x490.jpg 735w, https://walrus-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/img/ArchivalIssue_2023_Roundup_1800_02_Fiction-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://walrus-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/img/ArchivalIssue_2023_Roundup_1800_02_Fiction-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https://walrus-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/img/ArchivalIssue_2023_Roundup_1800_02_Fiction-348x232.jpg 348w" sizes="(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px" /><div style="max-width: 1500px;" class="special-series-body beauty-series">
<STORY START></p>
<div class="special-series-body">
<p><span class="dropcap">O</span><span class="smallcaps">ver the past</span> twenty years, The Walrus has been a steady bellwether of must-read writing. For our 20th anniversary, we’ve collected works that still surprise us, impress us, move us. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Here are some of the best pieces of short fiction that we’ve published.</p>
